   maximizing class separation while minimizing misclassification errors,
   and it is computationally more efficient than a previous formulation. We
   present a kernel-based extension that allows it to construct nonlinear
   decision boundaries. Furthermore, we show how the framework can
   naturally incorporate alternative geometric structures, including
   classification trees, \&
